<h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>

<p>This widget is based on <a href="https://github.com/jsspencer">@jsspencer</a>â€™ <a href="https://github.com/jsspencer/pomo">pomo</a> - a simple pomodoro timer.
So first install/clone it anywhere you like, then either</p>
<ul>
  <li>in widgetâ€™s code provide path to the pomo.sh, or</li>
  <li>add pomo.sh to the PATH, or</li>
  <li>make a soft link in /usr/local/bin/ to it:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> <span class="nb">sudo ln</span> <span class="nt">-sf</span> /opt/pomodoro/pomo.sh /usr/local/bin/pomo
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>Note that by default widgetâ€™s code expects third way and calls script by <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">pomo</code>.</p>
